===Etymology===
From earlier {{term|Godby|lang=en}}, {{term|Godby'e|lang=en}}, {{term|Godbwye|lang=en}}, {{term|God b'w'y|lang=en}}, {{term|God bwy yee|lang=en}}, {{term|God buy you|lang=en}}, {{term|God be wi' you|lang=en}}: each a progressively shorter contraction of {{term||[[God]] [[be]] [[with]] [[you]]}}, with change of {{term|God|lang=en}} to {{term|good|lang=en}} by confusion with {{term|good morning|lang=en}}, {{term|good day|lang=en}}, etc.

